Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.26,0:00:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. David R. Hawkins.\NAll right, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.34,0:00:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Dr. Dr. David Hawkins,\Nte riang sung kak to sa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.68,0:00:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NWell, that is all fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.42,0:01:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're here today to go over a difficult but simple subject.\NAnd the way to learn the most difficult subject on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing as it's eluded the consciousness of mankind up to this moment,\Nis to just listen with interest, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.70,0:01:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to use your intellect.\NThere's nothing that you can intellectually wrap around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.70,0:01:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of familiarity.\NAnd familiarity, strangely enough, changes one's whole context
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.73,0:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and feeling about reality.\NAnd so we're just going to cover what consciousness research has turned up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.02,0:01:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's been unique\Nin my own work
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.02,0:01:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it signifies about life and consciousness and spiritual reality.\NThe other thing we're going to do is we're going to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.02,0:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of the audience before and after.\NWe have permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do this. Resist.\NConsciousness level of this audience is over 350. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:01:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,360. Resist.\N370. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.40,0:02:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,390. Resist.\N400. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.40,0:02:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,420. Resist.\N410. 410. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,411. Over 410. Over 411.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.84,0:02:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have an audience that calibrates at 410.\NThat's very bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.84,0:02:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see what that means in a minute.\NIt means you're wide awake and able to comprehend what we're going to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a relief.\NAnd if I calibrate an audience and their mind is 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.84,0:02:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,uh-oh, it's going to be a tough day.\NAll right, so what we're going to be covering today
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.87,0:02:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is the whole field of consciousness.\NWe're going to recontextualize the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's place in it.\NWhat mankind is all about from the beginning of time up to the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to cover evolution versus revolution.\NEvolution versus creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind of God.\NAnd that will be enough for the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.31,0:03:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself is probably the most rewarding study\Nof any subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.82,0:03:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause through consciousness, through a simple observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds and hundreds of seeming problems instantly dissolve.\NAnd they dissolve by letting go a specific point of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And those of you who are into spiritual work,\Nthere's a good deal of discussion about the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a whole chart of the levels of the ego from 200 down.\NTranscend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.74,0:03:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego really arises from positionality.\NTaking an arbitrary point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you take an arbitrary point of view,\Nyou have now created a duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.00,0:03:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No duality exists in reality with a capital R.\NBut in reality with a small r,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.13,0:04:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in which most of society lives,\Nthey live in a world of constant dualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is created by the positionality.\NLet's take a positionality of good and bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.26,0:04:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you're caught by good and bad,\Nyour life is now somewhat considerably down the tubes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because at every moment you have a conflict between\Nwhat seems to be a conflict, a contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.48,0:04:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start with the end.\NWe'll start with the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.54,0:04:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take as an example the academic argument\Nwhich is in the headlines having to do with creation versus evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposedly there's a conflict\Nbetween creation and evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.54,0:04:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is intensely political\Nand people get red in the face and argue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.90,0:04:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been in the court system.\NAnd the minute you hear something versus something,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:05:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize right away there's an artificiality here.\NNo such thing really exists in reality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because in reality there is no conflict.\NAny conflict that you see has to be made up by the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.90,0:05:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a positionality.\NA positionality of either-or-ness, either-or-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.18,0:05:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let us say that that which is the infinite divinity,\Nthat which is the unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the manifest universe,\Nbeyond time, space, locality,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is infinite obviously has neither beginning nor end.\NNeither beginnings nor end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.04,0:05:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, with a little reflection,\Nyou will see that if there is such a thing as creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.04,0:05:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it is either continuous,\Nalways ongoing and forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.10,0:05:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or it never did occur.\NThere's nothing in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinite cannot do a thing once.\NThere would have to be a beginning and a stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.22,0:06:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, beginnings and stoppings are within man's consciousness.\NThat thing begins when you say it begins
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.61,0:06:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it ends when you say it ends.\NBut that's all in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no beginning and no ending out there.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.62,0:06:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation, to be comprehensible\Nfor an understanding of the nature of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of God,\Nwould have to be forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is always continuous.\NAnd the unfolding of creation, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the unfolding of creation,\Nappears as evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.32,0:06:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, evolution and creation are one and the same thing.\NAnd evolution is merely
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.32,0:06:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the unfolding of creation to man's perception.\NAs you see it arise, you think it is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only happening to your observation.\NSo if creation and evolution are one and the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,once you drop two different points of view,\Nyou see there is no conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If creation occurs, then it would...\NHow would it appear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,From nothingness to allness?\NNo, because we see, even during recorded time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,things change.\NSo things in an infinite time duration
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.04,0:07:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can't begin to change and then stop.\NThey're either ongoing or they never were.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.17,0:07:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be an example\Nof how one transcends a seeming paradox,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a seeming conflict,\Nby merely expanding context.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.16,0:07:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the other thing we're going to do today is,\Neverything we say is verifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to start, perhaps,\Nwith an explanation of the technique we have used
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.18,0:07:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to do a lot of this research.\NAnd this brings us to understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.30,0:07:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of consciousness itself.\NThe universe can be looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.97,0:07:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of the linear.\NThat is form.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.13,0:08:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the Newtonian paradigm of reality,\Nin which this causes this, causes this, causes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.45,0:08:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In that paradigm of reality,\Ncause exists within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, what causes this?\NAnd reality is looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.15,0:08:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,like a series of billiard balls.\NA hits B, B hits C, that hits D.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.15,0:08:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is called causation.\NThat's the world that we have delineated
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.20,0:08:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from 200 down.\NThat's the world of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.20,0:08:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world of science.\NIt goes up to the level of 400,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of logic.\NAnd the world of form,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.30,0:08:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear world,\Nis solvable,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.55,0:08:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as described by Sir Isaac Newton,\Nby the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.32,0:08:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is beyond the differential calculus\Neludes the understanding of the scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.32,0:08:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The scientist limits himself\Nto the mechanical, physical world
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.86,0:09:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and says, unless you can measure it,\Nit's not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This presumes, then,\Nthat there's an objective reality
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists independent of consciousness.\NAnd if we sent machines out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.89,0:09:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it could measure it and report back to us.\NSo, the paradigm of science
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then ends in the 400s.\NThe world in which people exist
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.98,0:09:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,really goes from the 400s up to 1000.\NHuman life is lived
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.02,0:09:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the non-linear domain.\NNon-linear, meaning not measurable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.18,0:09:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not weighable, not photographable.\NHuman consciousness is where we all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.56,0:09:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,experience all of life subjectively.\NSo, reality with a capital R, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.26,0:09:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is purely subjective.\NReality with a small r is objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual reality\Nis non-measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.10,0:10:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't identify and measure\Nhow much happiness, how much love,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,how much peace, how much serenity a person has,\Nor how much value or meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,something has to a person.\NHowever, that's the level in which we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.02,0:10:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the invisible domain.\NFrom the invisible domain of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.63,0:10:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we witness, we observe,\Nwe become conscious, we're aware
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.63,0:10:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of a linear world.\NBut that's really out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.02,0:10:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the in here that's aware of the out there.\NAnd it's in the in here that we have our existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.02,0:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our in here, in here,\Nthat which is the self behind the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to be talking today\Nabout two different domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.67,0:10:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Self with a small s, which is the world of the ego,\Nwhich is the way most people define themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.93,0:10:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people define themselves\Nas how much money they have, how good looking they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all these feelings of shame, guilt, apathy,\Nthat's the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the realm of the self with a small s.\NThat's the realm which people seek to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.93,0:11:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're involved in spiritual work,\Nif they're in the 12-step program,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're trying to advance to higher levels of consciousness.\NTo transcend the identification of I as body,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I as mind, I as a separate ego,\Nand realize that behind the word I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.57,0:11:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is a greater I.\NThe only reason that I can say I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is because that which is not an individual\Ngives me consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.43,0:11:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's that which we witness,\Nthen there's that which witnesses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the observer, the experiencer.\NBehind that is awareness, consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself has no form.\NIt's like the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.54,0:12:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the water,\Nand the thoughts are like the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.22,0:12:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is like the water,\Nit observes the fish going through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.22,0:12:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But consciousness is\Nunaffected by what goes through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.22,0:12:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit is unaffected by what goes through it.\NWell, we got interested in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.10,0:12:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and began using a technique called kinesiology.\NThere's a number of different techniques you can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we became aware that\Ndifferent levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,have different relative levels of power,\Nand that these could be calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,relative to each other, relative to each other.\NAnd we came up with, it suggested itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.52,0:12:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as answers to the questions arose,\Na calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that went from one to a thousand.\NSo a little germ, the minute it appears on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.65,0:12:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at one already.\NTo get anywhere, you've got to start at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.99,0:13:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness then moves on up through the animal kingdom\Nas awareness progresses,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and kinesiology is a simple test,\Nwhich I'll also teach you before we leave today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.98,0:13:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are a number of other ways\Nof achieving the same numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And we asked, if existence is one,\Nwhat's the greatest number of any being
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.27,0:13:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that ever walked the planet?\NAnd the answer we got was one thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll just show you how we did it.\NWe have permission to do this calibration resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.38,0:13:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of mankind goes all the way up to one thousand resist.\NPeople who've walked this earth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,have calibrated over a thousand resist.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.73,0:13:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand is the level of the avatar resist.\NBuddha, Christ, Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.73,0:13:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.\NAll right, so reality then goes from one to a thousand,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:14:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which one thousand then is the highest energy field\Nwhich protoplasm apparently can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.66,0:14:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy beyond that would be sort of fry.\NSo a thousand is as high as it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.66,0:14:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a thousand I presume are angelic realms.\NLet's just see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.69,0:14:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a thousand is angelic realms.\NOver a thousand is angelic realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get a physical body anymore.\NAll right, so from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting.\NWell, we found that at a certain level
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a difference between truth and falsehood.\NAnd this is probably the most interesting thing we've discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.69,0:14:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level, kinesiology can tell the difference\Nbetween truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said, what is the number of that level?\NAnd it gave us 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the level of truth.\NThis is the level of 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.90,0:15:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that calibrates above 200 makes your arm go strong.\NAnything below 200 is false,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.02,0:15:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive, what the world calls evil,\Nand will make your arm go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.02,0:15:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, this level differentiates two different realms,\Ntwo different polarities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.25,0:15:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the positive and the negative, the true and the false,\Nthe constructive and the negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.25,0:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the constructive and the destructive.\NInterestingly enough, it infallibly tells the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tells truth from falsehood.\NIt infallibly tells truth from falsehood about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Inasmuch as consciousness is beyond time and space\Nand is universally present everywhere throughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.24,0:15:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that has ever happened,\Nevery thought that's ever been thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.26,0:15:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,every event that has occurred\Nis registered forever in the energy field called consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.26,0:15:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A nonlinear domain in which the vibration,\Nthe frequency, the signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the unique signal of every thought,\Nevery feeling that ever occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.38,0:16:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere, by anything or anyone,\Nis registered forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.73,0:16:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not surprising, scripture says,\Nnot a hair shall be lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,every sparrow shall be counted.\NAnd we find kinesiologically that is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.98,0:16:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That at this time and place,\Nanybody here in this audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll do it for relief,\Ncan pick the person next to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can find out anything about anywhere,\Nanybody or anything that ever existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.72,0:16:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in the universe,\Nanywhere in time or space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not confined to this planet.\NI'm not confined to any domain whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible if you realize the nature of nonlinear reality.\NNonlinear means non-dimensional.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It means beyond time, beyond space, beyond form.\NAdvanced theoretical physics approaches this realm,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.64,0:16:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get below the alpha neutrino.\NYou come to things that no longer have physical existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They exist almost as a potentiality.\NThey exist as a position,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.64,0:17:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a possible position of energy, perhaps,\Nwith a certain polarity and a certain charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.79,0:17:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So these energy fields which dominate human consciousness,\Nthen, were calibratable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.85,0:17:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We did such things as calibrated\Nthe actual power of a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is an interesting thing,\Nthat the power of a loving thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.39,0:17:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,let me see if I get this right,\Nthe power of a loving thought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.10,0:17:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is 2 to the minus 3.5 million microwatts.\NThe power of a hateful or fearful thought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.86,0:17:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is 1 to the minus 750 million microwatts.\NWell, that was a profound finding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.86,0:17:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause what it means is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.98,0:17:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a loving thought is so enormously more powerful\Nthan a negative thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can think negative thoughts all day,\Nand as long as you end up feeling the loving courage of your kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and love your mother and kiss your wife at night,\Nyou're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.98,0:18:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A loving thought undoes all the horrid thoughts\Nthat you feel so guilty about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's look at the energy level of guilt.\NGuilt calibrates at 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.98,0:18:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very, very weak.\NYou can feel guilty for years and years and years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.98,0:18:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and other than blowing out your heart rate\Nand then killing yourself with a heart attack or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.98,0:18:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't really do much harm on the planet.\NBecause the lady next door loves her dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.98,0:18:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and her loving vibrations go out\Nand cancel out all your negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is good to know.\NYou don't have to be afraid of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.46,0:18:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have it all you want.\NShame is 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.46,0:18:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is 30.\NApathy is 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.66,0:19:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the amazing thing we discovered is...\NYou see, what we discovered is sort of like...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.78,0:19:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this is about the year 1509,\Nand the telescope has just been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're practically at that same thing.\NWe suddenly have a new instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in which whole new dimensions of the universe\Nbecome readily apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And at first they seem mind-boggling,\Nbut as you reflect on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.78,0:19:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly it all fits together, you see.\NOh, now I understand why such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 85% of mankind,\N85% of the people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate below 200.\NHmm, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.58,0:19:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've got shame, guilt, and apathy.\NThat's starvation, grief, despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.58,0:19:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,people being arrested, in jail, prison, fear.\NWe have war, suicide, desire, addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,anger, rage, hatred, pridefulness.\NOh, whoa, what a big one that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here, below 200,\Neverybody goes weak, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:20:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, now, what is...\NWhen we do this demonstration,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.08,0:20:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to test some people\Nthat are obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.27,0:20:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,not in great spiritual favor, likely.\NYou know, Hitler calibrates over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, sorry.\NHe did calibrate over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.50,0:20:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's over 300 resist.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so things change, anyway.\NThat which is negative or false,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.80,0:20:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if I say...\NSay my name is Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.05,0:20:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Helen.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.05,0:20:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is not Helen.\NSay her name is Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Susan.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Susan, yes.\NWe've actually calibrated credit card numbers using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.46,0:20:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody sent us one,\Nand they didn't put the date on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.46,0:20:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We just went through it,\Nwent through the machine, it was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,\N200 delineates
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.58,0:21:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of destructive negativity and falsity.\NOver 200 is positive, it's true, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we go over 200,\Nwhich is the level of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.02,0:21:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the capacity to tell the truth.\NThe capacity to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.02,0:21:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The first step in the 12-step programs,\Nyou stop lying and you admit the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.02,0:21:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You admit the truth that you're powerless\Nover this, that, and the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first on the way back,\Nbecause it takes you over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,250 is the level of trusting and easy-goingness.\NPeople at 250 are very easy to get along with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I like people at 250.\NThey say, you know, if I get the job, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.31,0:21:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't, I'll get another one.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.31,0:21:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't panic.\NThey don't commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.31,0:21:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't go into rages and punch you\Nbecause they didn't get the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.31,0:21:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They just say, well, you like me, fine.\NYou don't like me, you don't like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're wonderful people.\NTheir willingness, of course, is even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.14,0:22:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness at 310.\NIf you have a waitress at New Challenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.14,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,she says, what do you have today?\NAnd then if you get a waitress at Willingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,she says, oh, hi, doc.\NAre you going to have the regular?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.33,0:22:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, now she gets a bigger tip, doesn't she?\NWillingness makes the greatest employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We love people at Willingness\Nbecause they're the helpers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.00,0:22:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the people you need to get things done.\NThey're the workers of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.00,0:22:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,350 is acceptance.\NThey would begin hitting such levels as forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.00,0:22:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People are transcending.\NAbout 350, they're transcending good and bad
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.00,0:22:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and beginning to see things more through understanding.\NAnd good and bad is not really so relevant anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.00,0:22:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really sort of immaterial now whether it's good or bad.\NIt's more important if it works, if it brings peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.00,0:22:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the direction we're working.\NLove at 500 is relatively rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This level of love is, at 540,\Nit reaches unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.06,0:23:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12-step groups curiously enough calibrated 540.\N540 is the level of healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.06,0:23:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Severe diseases cannot be cured with energy levels less than 540.\NIt takes the level almost miraculous of 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.06,0:23:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Quits is the level of serenity and unconditional love.\NI think 0.4% of the world's population reaches that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.06,0:23:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 500.\NWe have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.31,0:23:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the population ever reaches 500 resist.\NEver reaches 540 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Over 500.\N0.4% of the world's population resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.62,0:23:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,These things change somewhat, so we have to recheck them periodically.\NBut approximately 0.4% of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.68,0:24:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,reaches a level you could call unconditional love.\NTherefore you see how rare true love really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.74,0:24:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And unconditional means no matter what.\NAnd 600 is the level of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.89,0:24:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an infinite peace.\NAnd on the way there you go through joy and exquisite beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.89,0:24:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The high 500s are usually spiritual,\Nwell-known spiritual leaders in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.33,0:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pope is at about 570.\NThe fellow out of Tibet, what's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.42,0:24:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those are the high 500s.\NThat's about 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.42,0:24:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pope is about 570.\NSo they're great world spiritual leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.55,0:24:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600 there's a major transition.\NThat's the level of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.55,0:25:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear domain disappears as an existent reality.\NIt's usually experienced as infinite bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.95,0:25:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And from 700 up you have the high and extremely rare.\NSpiritual geniuses you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,900 and up is about 4 on the planet.\NOne being at 1000 totally balances the entire negativity of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.04,0:25:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So it only takes one avatar to counterbalance the entire negativity of the entire human race.\NWe found something interesting the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.36,0:25:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between the Buddha and Jesus Christ?\NA lot of people say, what is the difference between the two of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.90,0:25:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously two great beings.\NAnd some people switch from one to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.90,0:25:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They go to Christian for a while, and they go to Buddha for a while, and they go to Christian for a while, and then they go to...\NThey think, what is the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.90,0:25:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a difference?\NWell, they both calibrate at 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.90,0:25:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So does Krishna.\NSo we say, what is the difference if these beings all calibrate at 1000?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.90,0:26:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got the Buddha was a teacher of enlightenment.\NThe Buddha does not talk about salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.70,0:26:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't talk about heaven.\NTalks about enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.70,0:26:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as the Buddha said, very few people are equipped for that.\NAnd more practically speaking, Christ said, or Christ came to save people below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.38,0:26:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said, Christ's mission was to die for the people who are below 200.\NWe said, are the people below 200 destined for heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.38,0:26:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, no.\NAnd then Christ's mission was that of salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.20,0:26:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That of salvation.\NThat for all those who are below 200 do not have the spiritual energy, insight, or assistance to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.33,0:27:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And without the help of a very high guru, you might say.\NThat's in accordance with Eastern religions also.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.00,0:27:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that you cannot reach really a high level without an advanced spiritual teacher.\NSo they had two different missions, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.00,0:27:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's what we came up with.\NYou don't have to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.00,0:27:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to believe anything I'm saying.\NBut that Buddha was to teach the way to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.00,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ was the way to salvation.\NAnd there is a branch of Buddhism called New Land Buddhism which takes the same position.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.00,0:27:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But the likelihood of becoming enlightened on this extremely negative plane here is quite limited.\NBut if you follow a spiritual pathway, then at the time of death, the Buddha of salvation will take you to the lotus heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.03,0:27:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,From there you can go to enlightenment.\NSo there's a number of positions then that enlightenment is not possible for the average person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.38,0:28:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to be pretty fixed in one point of the mind and probably considered quite strange by everybody around you.\NSo now, we wanted to cover the things in the syllabus here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.77,0:28:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to cover the difference between...\NWe wanted to cover the calibration levels of consciousness and how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.12,0:28:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought next...\NAny of you would like to learn how to do kinesiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.12,0:28:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody want to learn it?\NOkay, we'll just...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do this.\NI'll tell you what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.12,0:28:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to divide up into ones and twos.\NPick somebody near you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.15,0:28:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just...\NThere's just one exercise from that point on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.15,0:28:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it yourself.\NThe person who's tested, we ask them to hold in mind somebody they love.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.86,0:28:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have them resist.\NSo we'll demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.98,0:28:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can find out the truth about anything with this, by the way.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.55,0:28:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The car that I'm intending to buy is, you know, really good and solid.\NWe...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.55,0:28:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NOkay, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.87,0:28:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing she does is close her eyes so she's not distracted.\NYou don't have music in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.87,0:29:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Music will affect it.\NShe doesn't have any metal across the midline.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.87,0:29:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She tries to keep her mind blank.\NAnd I ask permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.22,0:29:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do this demonstration today.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.22,0:29:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Says yes.\NWe have permission for this audience to do this demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.22,0:29:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold in mind something or someone you love.\NIt can be your kitty, your mother, president of your country, spiritual figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.29,0:29:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NMother Teresa.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.29,0:29:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold in mind Mother Teresa.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.29,0:29:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay, now hold in mind that awful person from childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.93,0:29:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NI know who it is, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.93,0:29:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that the sixth grade teacher?\NShe had a monster teacher in sixth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.25,0:29:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the demonstration is merely love makes you go strong and non-love makes you go weak.\NTruth makes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.25,0:30:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsity makes you go weak.\NIt seems like a simple thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.18,0:30:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After we've learned how to do it, I'll tell you what you can do with it, besides becoming an overnight millionaire.\NOkay, so let's all just go ones and twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.62,0:30:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two.\NYou want to just choose next to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.62,0:30:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just do it real quickly.\NI'll show you through experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.62,0:30:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to join this.\NThis is all voluntary.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.62,0:30:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody doesn't have to.\NDon't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.62,0:30:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, if the subject of kinesiology comes up, you can say, yes, I went to electronic.\NWe tried it, and this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.62,0:30:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The easiest way is to smile, basically.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.03,0:30:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now you decide which one's going to be the doctor, which one's the patient, who's number one, and who's number two.\NOkay, number one, you're going to be the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.77,0:31:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ask, this is your patient here.\NCome over here, patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.77,0:31:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just hold your arm out like this patient, please.\NAnd when I press down, I'm going to press with two fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.77,0:31:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to test out her relative strength.\NI'm not trying to break her arm down or win a game or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.77,0:31:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, when I say resist, resist, resist.\NSee, I'm pushing with one finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.09,0:31:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell her to resist.\NWhen you resist, try to just equalize the pressure that's being pressed on you, you know, so that your arm stays the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.09,0:31:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I press down, I push back up equal to the pressure.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.09,0:31:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, picture Mother Teresa.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.41,0:31:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NOkay, so you can all just picture someone you love and ask the person that you're testing to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.41,0:31:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them close their eyes.\NJust say to them, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you all got Mother Teresa.\NYou all got love.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.46,0:32:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your kitty in mind, your favorite dog, your favorite school teacher, whoever.\NOkay, now we ask the person that we're testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.93,0:32:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture somebody you know you don't love, somebody you're afraid of.\NSome unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.93,0:32:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture yourself being run over by a railroad train.\NAnd then ask them to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.93,0:32:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that you know darn well is non-love.\NThere are some unlovable people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.59,0:32:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold that in mind.\NSaddam Hussein was always doing a pinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.59,0:32:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It might.\NI doubt it, but it might.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.97,0:32:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, across the midnight.\NYou try to avoid middle across the midnight, mainly glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.97,0:32:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't have to worry about it unless you see it's interfering.\NIf you don't get the correct answers, then some of these things you've got to pay more attention to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:33:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, does love make everybody go strong?\NDoes love make anybody go weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.62,0:33:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And non-love makes you go weak.\NSo all I want you to experience is the energy of love versus the energy of not love.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.62,0:33:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NOkay, now we can reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.62,0:33:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ones and twos, switch doctor and patient.\NYeah, we'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.92,0:33:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAsk your patient to picture somebody they love.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.18,0:33:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them close their eyes.\NTake off their glasses if it's metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.55,0:33:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Just say, picture somebody you love.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.55,0:34:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,After you picture somebody you love and experience it, it makes you strong.\NPicture something fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.24,0:34:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Disgraceful.\NShameful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.24,0:34:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that serial killer?\NYour dog being run over by a truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.21,0:34:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everybody get that love makes you go strong?\NOkay, we can sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.41,0:35:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're experiencing, I want you to understand the nature of what we're experiencing.\NBecause the major jump in consciousness was the seeing that this response is not local.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.43,0:35:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-local.\NNow I'll explain what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.43,0:35:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology has been used by chiropractors, holistic health practitioners, physicians\Nall over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.56,0:35:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned it back in the 70s from Dr. John Diamond, who had learned it from George Goodhart,\Nwho was a chiropractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.56,0:35:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Diamond took it to a different level.\NHe took it to the level of, which I'll demonstrate, a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.56,0:35:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to demonstrate.\NAnyway, he took it to a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.23,0:35:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That not only do physical things locally make you strong or weak, but there's certain things\Nthat make you strong or weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.23,0:35:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's certain attitudes or designs or figures that make you go as strong or weak.\NLet's just, we should have had you do this before you sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.90,0:35:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to all stand up again?\NWe'll just do it real quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.90,0:35:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the patients, okay, let's go back to the ones and the twos that we had the first time.\NOkay, patients, I want you to look at this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.25,0:36:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the patients to look at the figure going like this.\NLook at this picture and then ask the person to test you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.11,0:36:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NLook at that picture and say, doctor, say resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.43,0:36:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that picture, patient, and say resist.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.43,0:36:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.82,0:36:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, patients, now look at this image.\NLook at this image over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.77,0:36:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now ask the patient to resist again while they're looking at that image.\NOkay, now we can switch doctor and patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.94,0:36:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, patients, I want you to look at the smile.\NTest the patient who's looking at a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.57,0:37:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell him to resist.\NAnd then look at what, there's a negative-looking person's mouth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.50,0:37:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI just wanted to give you some examples because people, I want you to understand that what
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.23,0:37:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we discovered was that the kinesiologic response is the response of consciousness itself.\NIt is not a local response.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.23,0:37:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people, when they see this, they say, well, the response is going to depend on what\Nthe person you're testing believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.23,0:37:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it has nothing to do with what the person you're testing believes.\NIn fact, very often, the result is the opposite of what the person you're testing believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.23,0:38:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the nature of consciousness itself.\NNow, we look at protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.23,0:38:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Protoplasm, its response is impersonal.\NYou stick it with a needle, it bleeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.23,0:38:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impersonal.\NThat's not George bleeding or Pete bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.23,0:38:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's protoplasm bleeding.\NIt has nothing to do with your personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.81,0:38:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness has nothing to do with your personality.\NConsciousness responds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.81,0:38:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows truth from non-truth, and that's all it knows.\NThe only thing consciousness knows is truth from non-truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.81,0:38:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It instantly knows that.\NThat's not surprising that the essence of life itself, like an amoeba, would know what's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.51,0:38:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,good for it, and it would move towards that which is life-giving, and that it would draw\Nfrom that which is destructive of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.74,0:38:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, then, which is everywhere present at all times.\NEqually, it only knows one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.18,0:38:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows truth.\NThat's really all it knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.18,0:38:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even know falsehood.\NFalsehood is only a way of speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.18,0:39:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It only knows truth.\NIt knows whether truth is present or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.18,0:39:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it knows.\NWell, we've just said probably the most profound thing in the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.66,0:39:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Innate within us is the capacity to know truth from falsehood.\NMankind, since the beginning of time, has been completely unable to know truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.43,0:39:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To know truth from falsehood.\NEvery battle ever lost in the history of this world was due to the loss of not knowing what
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.49,0:39:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the other side was doing.\NThey're going to go around the Maginot Line, not through it, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.02,0:39:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to go through the Ardennes Forests.\NEvery single battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.02,0:39:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have said, did he move the 8th Battalion?\NOr didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.06,0:39:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He did.\NOh, we would have won that war, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.06,0:40:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done it.\NTake every member of the State Department, every employee of the State Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.70,0:40:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you who's a mole and who's not a mole within about one second.\NEvery mole in the State Department, in the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.70,0:40:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you look at their picture and you say, this man is an integrist, this man is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.74,0:40:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,an integrist, this man is an integrist.\NWham.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.74,0:40:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There you've got the greatest spy there who lived.\NI had him years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.15,0:40:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the applications are rather stupendous.\NI have at home the Greek Books of the Western World, a very impressive series of documents
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.57,0:40:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,put out by the University of Chicago faculty back in the 30s, I think.\NA whole shelf of the greatest thinkers of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.34,0:40:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Greatest, right all the way down as far as before, I think it was the last volume.\NOh, he got in there, I don't know, but he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.26,0:40:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The content of the greatest books that have ever lived, the greatest wines that have ever\Nlived, has been a discussion, all 50 volumes or whatever, is trying to decide what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.74,0:40:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't know.\NWhat do you need a jury for?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.74,0:41:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't know what's truth.\NWhat do you need witness for?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.12,0:41:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you have to record it?\NWhy do you have to videotape it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.12,0:41:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the human mind, unaided, is unable to know truth from falsehood.\NThat was Eve's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.40,0:41:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Eve's problem.\NThat's everybody's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.40,0:41:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is...\NAlright, so we can use this analogy, the human mind, innate consciousness itself is like
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.40,0:41:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware, and the ego is like the software.\NThe ego is like the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.32,0:41:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The software, the ego, is unable to know truth.\NIt doesn't know truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.64,0:41:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no mechanism and no means to know truth from falsehood.\NWe're told, beware the wolf in sheep's clothing, but you're not told how to tell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.89,0:42:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know the sheep in wolf's clothing?\NThe church didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.89,0:42:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The church was invaded by all kinds of destructive and negative people who carried enemy but\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.89,0:42:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the church itself could not defend itself against the lie.\NSo, until this time, mankind has had no means of knowing truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.46,0:42:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say the research done by Edison, research done by Edison, which took, I forget, 14 years\Nand $350 million, we can come to the same answer with about five questions in less than
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.68,0:42:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,two minutes, thereby saving 14 years and $250 million.\NSo it's application in research, in science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.61,0:42:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's application in, to me, intelligence, military intelligence.\NYou can tell that there is a true painting and a false painting in an instant, and I've
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.25,0:43:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,got both of them at home.\NI've got the real thing, and if you wrap it all up in newspaper and hold it like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.54,0:43:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes you go strong.\NAnd I have a very excellent Picasso, and this Picasso makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.66,0:43:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell that one quick and get out of town.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.66,0:43:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, the greatest art galleries in the world, the greatest national, what\Ndo you call it, in Washington, had huge, in the last 10 years, a big major every expert
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.66,0:43:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world trying to decide whether a certain painting was legitimate or not.\NYou're talking about millions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.66,0:43:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's legitimate, it's probably worth $50 million.\NIf it's not, it's probably worth, you know, a couple thousand, because it was a good fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.02,0:43:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it has many, many applications.\NSo we have these levels of consciousness, which...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.91,0:43:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you become familiar with the levels of consciousness, it's quite difficult not\Nto keep growing spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.91,0:44:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's practically impossible.\NOnce you've even seen the map of consciousness and become aware of it, your mind begins to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.58,0:44:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically seek a higher level.\NIt just automatically begins to want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.58,0:44:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We have in the synopsis on the first page the difference between the linear and the\Nnonlinear domains, which, by the time you read it, it becomes quite obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.58,0:44:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, although this may, to some people, unless it's explained correctly, seem extremely\Ndifficult or complicated, it's really quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.32,0:44:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's laid out in front of you, your mind just says, oh, yeah, I always knew that.\NIn a way, what we're doing today is merely recontextualizing what your mind only knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.76,0:44:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And now its meaning becomes significant.\NIts meaning becomes quite clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.53,0:44:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have, for instance...\NHow the mind thinks in a linear way is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.17,0:45:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's local.\NIt depends on force rather than power.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.30,0:45:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we said that the levels below 200 are levels of force.\NThe levels above 200 are levels of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.74,0:45:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the book is called Power Versus Force.\NLevels from 200 down are force.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.00,0:45:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Force.\NWhat is force?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.29,0:45:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Force...\NGoes from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.77,0:45:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Force goes from here to there.\NIn so doing, it expends energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.22,0:45:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, force, you have to constantly feed force.\NThe army gets bigger, it eats more.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.70,0:45:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger and more successful it is, the more complicated it becomes.\NForce gradually exhausts itself because it uses up energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.98,0:45:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It uses up energy.\NForce is therefore limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.43,0:46:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Force...\NForce is what people who don't have power resort to as a substitute for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.50,0:46:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200.\NThose are the things that people do who lack power.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.50,0:46:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to steal.\NThey have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.50,0:46:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to shoot.\NThey have to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.50,0:46:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to cheat.\NTo feel good, they have to take drugs and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.14,0:46:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...\NSo, force expends itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.14,0:46:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Force is what makes everything else work.\NWhat makes everything else work.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.58,0:46:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, over 200, are levels of power.\NThe difference between the two is that power does not move from one place to the other at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.77,0:46:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stationary.\NPower just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.77,0:46:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And by nature of its essence, it influences everything within its domain.\NSo power just stands there and, like gravity, controls everything within it without moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.77,0:46:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not expend energy.\NPower actually creates energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.99,0:47:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun just radiates forth.\NRadiates forth and nurtures all that it falls upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.99,0:47:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Power is also not selective.\NIt doesn't say, well, you're going to get a little grace and a little love and you're going to the other place.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.25,0:47:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are...\NThose are imaginations of the ego that such a thing is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.14,0:47:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, then, does not use energy.\NIt radiates energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.46,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're in the presence of somebody who has great power, we feel good, we feel energized, we feel inspired.\NSo power, then, is not local.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great power, the power of the great spiritual beings that have been here still reside within the field of human consciousness.\NThey remain to this day, can be calibrated to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.96,0:47:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be class is almost over.\NClass is over, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.96,0:47:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a five-minute break.\NAnd we're going to speak for a little while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.96,0:48:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, at the end, we'll ask for questions and any commentaries you wish to make.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.96,0:48:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
